776
00:43:52.083 --> 00:43:54.832
Anyway. you know what
the most important thing is

777
00:43:54.833 --> 00:43:56.292
for human survival?

778
00:43:56.667 --> 00:43:58.542
The number one thing.

779
00:43:59.958 --> 00:44:01.041
Positive attitude.

780
00:44:01.042 --> 00:44:02.625
Oh. are you fucking kidding me?

781
00:44:03.250 --> 00:44:05.082
We have to act. all right?

782
00:44:05.083 --> 00:44:06.999
I'm serious.
I'm sick of this shit.

783
00:44:07.000 --> 00:44:08.624
We have to do something. okay?

784
00:44:08.625 --> 00:44:10.624
We should build a raft
or something.

785
00:44:10.625 --> 00:44:12.082
- A what?
- Yeah.

786
00:44:12.083 --> 00:44:13.791
I saw a <i>60 Minutes</i> once

787
00:44:13.792 --> 00:44:15.166
of this guy.
he survived a shipwreck.

788
00:44:15.167 --> 00:44:16.416
He said he did three things.

789
00:44:16.417 --> 00:44:19.667
He saved food and water.
and he got found. okay?

790
00:44:19.958 --> 00:44:22.124
We have to go to where
the boats are. okay?

791
00:44:22.125 --> 00:44:25.208
We gotta-- We gotta find
shipping lanes. Get seen.

792
00:44:25.750 --> 00:44:26.749
Build a raft.

793
00:44:26.750 --> 00:44:28.458
I don't think
that's a good idea.

794
00:44:29.042 --> 00:44:30.750
A raft would be...

795
00:44:31.333 --> 00:44:35.125
I mean. I guess that's
an option. but as a last resort.

796
00:44:36.417 --> 00:44:37.666
No.

797
00:44:37.667 --> 00:44:39.542
We gotta keep doing
what we're doing.

798
00:44:40.583 --> 00:44:41.875
Stay the course.

799
00:44:43.042 --> 00:44:46.833
And anyway. honestly.
is it that bad?

800
00:44:47.375 --> 00:44:50.792
We have food. water. company.

801
00:44:51.708 --> 00:44:52.832
Linda. no disrespect.

802
00:44:52.833 --> 00:44:55.750
but this is the last place
on Earth that I'd want to be.

803
00:45:00.292 --> 00:45:01.458
Ouch.

804
00:45:02.667 --> 00:45:04.166
Haven't I taken
good care of you?

805
00:45:04.167 --> 00:45:05.792
Have you taken good care of me?

806
00:45:06.250 --> 00:45:07.625
Have you seen my face?

807
00:45:08.458 --> 00:45:10.500
Do you think my skin
is going to recover from this?

808
00:45:11.125 --> 00:45:14.500
- Huh?
- Look at you! You're thriving.

809
00:45:15.042 --> 00:45:16.791
(LAUGHS)

810
00:45:16.792 --> 00:45:19.458
This has turned into your life.
Yeah.

811
00:45:19.958 --> 00:45:21.582
What? What are you doing?

812
00:45:21.583 --> 00:45:22.499
I'm getting out of here.

813
00:45:22.500 --> 00:45:24.374
You can't put that kind
of weight on that. yet.

814
00:45:24.375 --> 00:45:27.125
You don't tell me what to do!
How about that?

815
00:45:27.792 --> 00:45:29.124
(GRUNTING)

816
00:45:29.125 --> 00:45:32.375
You know what?
You think you're so smart.

817
00:45:33.083 --> 00:45:34.750
Well. guess who
you're talking to?

818
00:45:35.750 --> 00:45:38.249
CEO of
a NextGen 500 company. baby.

819
00:45:38.250 --> 00:45:40.416
- That's right.
- (LAUGHS)

820
00:45:40.417 --> 00:45:43.082
A company your father built.

821
00:45:43.083 --> 00:45:44.625
God rest his soul.

822
00:45:45.792 --> 00:45:47.792
- (BOTH CHUCKLE)
- Oh. wow.

823
00:45:48.333 --> 00:45:49.957
Oh. wow. you know what?

824
00:45:49.958 --> 00:45:51.791
- You're so done.
- Huh?

825
00:45:51.792 --> 00:45:53.416
Yeah. you're so fired.

826
00:45:53.417 --> 00:45:54.541
Oh. am I?

827
00:45:54.542 --> 00:45:57.625
- Yeah.
- Oh. no. (GIGGLES)

828
00:45:58.583 --> 00:46:01.207
- Where are you going?
- Wherever the fuck I wanna go.

829
00:46:01.208 --> 00:46:02.916
- Making my own camp.
- Oh.

830
00:46:02.917 --> 00:46:04.082
It's not so hard.

831
00:46:04.083 --> 00:46:06.833
Just need some leaves
and some fucking sticks.

832
00:46:07.458 --> 00:46:08.708
I've seen you do it enough.

833
00:46:09.542 --> 00:46:12.249
Well. I wish you luck.

834
00:46:12.250 --> 00:46:15.042
And I'll tell you where
to send my last check.

835
00:46:15.583 --> 00:46:17.750
Second coconut tree on the left.

836
00:46:18.917 --> 00:46:20.333
That's a good rock.

837
00:46:22.542 --> 00:46:23.667
Good tree.

838
00:46:24.375 --> 00:46:25.583
Good foundation.

839
00:46:28.292 --> 00:46:29.708
This will be my home.

840
00:46:45.792 --> 00:46:47.042
Now we're cookin'.

841
00:47:24.958 --> 00:47:25.875
Ha!

842
00:47:29.875 --> 00:47:31.792
(HUMMING)

843
00:47:32.625 --> 00:47:35.582
- (BUGS BUZZING)
- (GRUNTING. PANTING)

844
00:47:35.583 --> 00:47:39.583
Oh. mmm. Mmm.

845
00:47:46.417 --> 00:47:47.708
(GRUNTS)

846
00:47:50.833 --> 00:47:51.750
(LAUGHS)

847
00:48:02.792 --> 00:48:04.792
(PANTING. GRUNTING)

848
00:48:13.750 --> 00:48:15.957
(HUMMING)

849
00:48:15.958 --> 00:48:16.917
Morning!

850
00:48:17.875 --> 00:48:19.125
(CHUCKLES SARCASTICALLY)
Hi.

851
00:48:23.167 --> 00:48:24.458
"Hepl"?

852
00:48:31.000 --> 00:48:32.375
(GROANS)

853
00:48:32.792 --> 00:48:34.125
(SIGHS)

854
00:48:38.292 --> 00:48:40.417
(GASPS)

855
00:48:41.833 --> 00:48:43.500
(GRUNTS)

856
00:48:51.500 --> 00:48:53.208
(PANTING)

857
00:48:54.542 --> 00:48:57.499
- (DELIRIOUS CHUCKLING)
- (CRUNCHES)

858
00:48:57.500 --> 00:48:59.583
Mmm. Mmm.

859
00:49:04.375 --> 00:49:07.250
(WHEEZING. CACKLING)

860
00:49:09.417 --> 00:49:11.250
(GAGGING)

861
00:49:12.292 --> 00:49:13.957
(COUGHING)

862
00:49:13.958 --> 00:49:18.166
(RETCHING. SCREAMING)

863
00:49:18.167 --> 00:49:20.125
(SPITS)

864
00:49:20.542 --> 00:49:22.916
(GROANS)

865
00:49:22.917 --> 00:49:24.582
(WHEEZES. SPITS)

866
00:49:24.583 --> 00:49:28.000
(EXHALING)

867
00:49:30.625 --> 00:49:32.791
(PANTING)

868
00:49:32.792 --> 00:49:33.917
You're beat.

869
00:49:39.542 --> 00:49:41.333
(HUMMING)

870
00:49:44.750 --> 00:49:46.833
(GASPING)
Hello.

871
00:49:49.125 --> 00:49:49.958
BRADLEY: Hello.

872
00:49:50.375 --> 00:49:51.333
Knock. knock.

873
00:49:52.208 --> 00:49:53.042
Hey.

874
00:49:53.792 --> 00:49:54.667
Linda?

875
00:49:55.292 --> 00:49:56.541
- LINDA: Mmm.
- Is that you?

876
00:49:56.542 --> 00:49:59.000
I think we met at
the Christmas party last year.

877
00:50:00.583 --> 00:50:02.874
Oh. Yes. I remember you.

878
00:50:02.875 --> 00:50:04.166
- Yes. Thought that was you.
- Mr. Preston?

879
00:50:04.167 --> 00:50:05.416
Yeah. That's right. How are you?

880
00:50:05.417 --> 00:50:06.707
- I'm great.
- (CHUCKLES)

881
00:50:06.708 --> 00:50:08.749
Oh. you have
a... something in your...

882
00:50:08.750 --> 00:50:10.542
Mmm.

883
00:50:10.833 --> 00:50:11.750
Oh. dear.

884
00:50:12.500 --> 00:50:14.332
(EXOSKELETON CRUNCHING)

885
00:50:14.333 --> 00:50:15.708
- Yeah.
- (SPITS)

886
00:50:16.625 --> 00:50:18.957
Wow. Check out the spread. huh?

887
00:50:18.958 --> 00:50:21.499
You know. I've paid
small fortunes for sushi

888
00:50:21.500 --> 00:50:22.792
that doesn't look that good.

889
00:50:23.208 --> 00:50:24.916
- Oh.
- Yeah.

890
00:50:24.917 --> 00:50:26.124
How much would you pay now?

891
00:50:26.125 --> 00:50:27.957
Oh. I'd kill for
what's on that plate.

892
00:50:27.958 --> 00:50:28.999
Mmm.

893
00:50:29.000 --> 00:50:30.832
But then what would you do
tomorrow?

894
00:50:30.833 --> 00:50:32.291
(LAUGHS)

895
00:50:32.292 --> 00:50:33.416
- Oops.
- Got me there.

896
00:50:33.417 --> 00:50:34.917
(LINDA CHUCKLES)

897
00:50:36.042 --> 00:50:37.582
- Mmm.
- Where did you get the knife?

898
00:50:37.583 --> 00:50:38.875
Oh!

899
00:50:39.292 --> 00:50:41.124
- I found it.
- (CHUCKLES)

900
00:50:41.125 --> 00:50:44.000
It is amazing the things
that just wash up on shore.

901
00:50:45.625 --> 00:50:47.250
Been a real lifesaver.

902
00:50:49.250 --> 00:50:50.125
So...

903
00:50:51.167 --> 00:50:53.917
What brings you
to my office today?

904
00:50:55.375 --> 00:50:56.833
I want to apologize.

905
00:50:57.792 --> 00:50:58.917
- What?
- Just for. uh...

906
00:50:59.458 --> 00:51:00.999
...the way that I acted.

907
00:51:01.000 --> 00:51:02.957
Here? Or when
we were back at your office?

908
00:51:02.958 --> 00:51:03.875
Both.

909
00:51:04.542 --> 00:51:06.292
I wanna take it all back.
Everything I said.

910
00:51:07.042 --> 00:51:08.207
So. I'm not fired?

911
00:51:08.208 --> 00:51:10.542
An asset like you?
Are you kidding me? (CHUCKLES)

912
00:51:11.333 --> 00:51:13.083
The company would be
in shambles without you.

913
00:51:13.500 --> 00:51:15.624
- Look at this place.
- Well. that is a relief.

914
00:51:15.625 --> 00:51:17.250
- Gotta say.
- Yeah. I'm glad.

915
00:51:18.083 --> 00:51:18.957
This looks amazing.

916
00:51:18.958 --> 00:51:21.499
You... look great.

917
00:51:21.500 --> 00:51:22.958
If you don't mind me saying.
Uh...

918
00:51:23.292 --> 00:51:24.167
I don't.

919
00:51:24.708 --> 00:51:27.042
Not even the same person who
walked into my office that day.

920
00:51:28.292 --> 00:51:31.666
So. would you say
you underestimated me?

921
00:51:31.667 --> 00:51:32.583
Yeah.

922
00:51:33.292 --> 00:51:35.832
I would say
I gravely underestimated you.

923
00:51:35.833 --> 00:51:37.291
That's exactly right.

924
00:51:37.292 --> 00:51:38.542
I was wrong.

925
00:51:39.167 --> 00:51:42.332
And I really. really
want to come back to camp.

926
00:51:42.333 --> 00:51:43.416
Hmm.

927
00:51:43.417 --> 00:51:46.042
And learn from you.
if you would have me. of course.

928
00:51:47.458 --> 00:51:49.750
(PANTING)

929
00:51:51.125 --> 00:51:53.624
(GULPING. EXHALES)

930
00:51:53.625 --> 00:51:57.167
Really? Well. I think
we could discuss that.

931
00:51:57.917 --> 00:51:59.416
- Okay.
- Would you like to sit down?

932
00:51:59.417 --> 00:52:01.416
- I would love to.
- Before you fall down.

933
00:52:01.417 --> 00:52:04.375
(CHUCKLES. GRUNTS)

934
00:52:05.583 --> 00:52:07.124
I was just thinking.
you know...

935
00:52:07.125 --> 00:52:08.500
Mm-hmm?

936
00:52:09.042 --> 00:52:12.416
I want to help.
As much as I can. I mean.

937
00:52:12.417 --> 00:52:14.499
I learned the hard way. You
make all this look really easy.

938
00:52:14.500 --> 00:52:16.624
But. I think
that's the best bet.

939
00:52:16.625 --> 00:52:18.207
Working as a team.

940
00:52:18.208 --> 00:52:20.832
You know?
That's a smart. smart play.

941
00:52:20.833 --> 00:52:21.791
That is smart.

942
00:52:21.792 --> 00:52:23.291
- Yes.
- Yes.

943
00:52:23.292 --> 00:52:26.249
Definitely smart on your part.
(CLEARS THROAT)

944
00:52:26.250 --> 00:52:28.792
"Linda." (WHEEZING LAUGH)

945
00:52:31.375 --> 00:52:32.375
So. what do you think?

946
00:52:32.750 --> 00:52:33.583
About what?

947
00:52:34.000 --> 00:52:35.749
Could you overlook
some of my character flaws?

948
00:52:35.750 --> 00:52:37.041
Of which there are many.

949
00:52:37.042 --> 00:52:39.125
(LAUGHS) And...

950
00:52:41.167 --> 00:52:43.375
...maybe I can join you
for lunch.

951
00:52:45.000 --> 00:52:47.749
Mmm. I don't know.

952
00:52:47.750 --> 00:52:48.917
Can I trust ya?

953
00:52:51.000 --> 00:52:53.458
- You can. (GROANING)
- (SLURPING)

954
00:52:56.583 --> 00:52:57.999
(GROANS)

955
00:52:58.000 --> 00:52:59.292
There was a little more on that.

956
00:53:01.625 --> 00:53:02.750
Linda. please.

957
00:53:03.083 --> 00:53:04.708
(WHISPERING) Please. Please.

958
00:53:06.208 --> 00:53:09.000
I'm sorry. (SIGHS)

959
00:53:10.708 --> 00:53:11.667
So. is that it?

960
00:53:13.875 --> 00:53:15.083
- Was that it?
- Is that your pitch?

961
00:53:18.583 --> 00:53:20.708
What do you want from me? Huh?

962
00:53:21.792 --> 00:53:22.875
Well. that depends.

963
00:53:24.833 --> 00:53:28.958
How above and beyond
are you willing to go for me?

964
00:53:35.000 --> 00:53:36.375
Hmm.

965
00:53:53.833 --> 00:53:56.542
Oh. I'm kidding. I'm kidding.
Just keep your shirt on.

966
00:53:56.917 --> 00:53:58.792
I would never do that.

967
00:54:01.042 --> 00:54:02.375
I'm not like you.

968
00:54:06.333 --> 00:54:08.000
(SIGHS) Enough.

969
00:54:09.083 --> 00:54:10.792
- Eat.
- (EXHALES)

970
00:54:11.958 --> 00:54:13.582
- (CACKLES)
- Enjoy.

971
00:54:13.583 --> 00:54:15.166
Thank you. Thank you. Thank you.

972
00:54:15.167 --> 00:54:17.041
- Here's some sauce.
- Thank you. Thank you.

973
00:54:17.042 --> 00:54:18.541
And I will get you
some more water.

974
00:54:18.542 --> 00:54:20.166
Thank you. (MOANS)

975
00:54:20.167 --> 00:54:22.458
- Mr. Bossypants.
- (MOANING) Oh. my God.

976
00:54:23.333 --> 00:54:26.916
What is that? (MOANS)

977
00:54:26.917 --> 00:54:29.208
Mmm.

978
00:54:31.208 --> 00:54:32.833
Mmm.

979
00:54:33.750 --> 00:54:34.583
Fuck.

980
00:54:35.833 --> 00:54:37.292
Ooh. mama.

981
00:54:43.833 --> 00:54:45.207
BRADLEY: (GRUNTING)

982
00:54:45.208 --> 00:54:47.458
Ah. what do you say
we take a walk?

983
00:54:48.167 --> 00:54:48.999
Sure.

984
00:54:49.000 --> 00:54:49.999
Your leg's getting
so much better.

985
00:54:50.000 --> 00:54:51.457
We should keep rehabbing it.

986
00:54:51.458 --> 00:54:52.542
Where are we going?

987
00:54:53.333 --> 00:54:54.208
Surprise.

988
00:54:56.417 --> 00:54:58.041
- You okay?
- Yeah.

989
00:54:58.042 --> 00:55:00.875
(BOTH PANTING)

990
00:55:18.875 --> 00:55:20.458
Okay. this spot's tough.

991
00:55:23.042 --> 00:55:24.667
This is the tricky bit.

992
00:55:27.875 --> 00:55:29.957
BRADLEY: (CLEARS THROAT)

993
00:55:29.958 --> 00:55:31.792
- You got it?
- (GRUNTING)

994
00:55:34.958 --> 00:55:36.457
- You got it.
- (GRUNTS)

995
00:55:36.458 --> 00:55:38.583
(BRIGHTLY) There we go.

996
00:55:39.417 --> 00:55:42.041
- Yeah.
- (CHUCKLES) Fun. right?

997
00:55:42.042 --> 00:55:43.624
- (CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)
- (CHUCKLES)

998
00:55:43.625 --> 00:55:44.833
Sure.

999
00:55:48.417 --> 00:55:50.417
(WIND WHISTLING)

1000
00:55:55.042 --> 00:55:56.583
Nothing for days.

1001
00:55:58.250 --> 00:55:59.499
(SIGHS)

1002
00:55:59.500 --> 00:56:00.958
That's us down there.

1003
00:56:02.458 --> 00:56:03.417
This way.

1004
00:56:06.958 --> 00:56:09.083
(BIRDS SQUAWKING)

1005
00:56:11.292 --> 00:56:12.792
Little foraging tip.

1006
00:56:14.000 --> 00:56:17.083
So. you never want to
eat a berry

1007
00:56:17.958 --> 00:56:19.875
that's yellow. green. or white.

1008
00:56:20.208 --> 00:56:22.542
But if you really wanna know
if it's poisonous or not...

1009
00:56:29.833 --> 00:56:32.666
If there's a reaction.
like that?

1010
00:56:32.667 --> 00:56:35.375
Yeah. yeah. Don't spread it
on your morning scone. got it.

1011
00:56:36.125 --> 00:56:37.957
(CHUCKLES) Funny.

1012
00:56:37.958 --> 00:56:40.041
All right. now down there.

1013
00:56:40.042 --> 00:56:42.416
you see that rock
that kinda looks like an X?

1014
00:56:42.417 --> 00:56:43.333
Yeah.

1015
00:56:43.625 --> 00:56:45.416
So. that part of the island.

1016
00:56:45.417 --> 00:56:48.250
it's all thorn bushes
and poison vines.

1017
00:56:48.917 --> 00:56:50.166
Three steps into that.

1018
00:56:50.167 --> 00:56:52.583
and you'll be scratching
your skin off for a week. so...

1019
00:56:53.792 --> 00:56:55.583
you don't want to
go that way. ever.

1020
00:56:56.875 --> 00:56:58.625
Okay.

1021
00:56:59.458 --> 00:57:00.624
All right. We should head back.

1022
00:57:00.625 --> 00:57:01.542
Yeah.

1023
00:57:02.750 --> 00:57:03.833
LINDA: Limpy McGee.

1024
00:57:06.333 --> 00:57:08.374
(WIND HOWLING)

1025
00:57:08.375 --> 00:57:11.500
I might give. uh. my leg
a breather for a minute.

1026
00:57:13.125 --> 00:57:14.292
- BRADLEY: (SIGHS)
- Yep.

1027
00:57:15.208 --> 00:57:16.292
Take your time.

1028
00:57:18.375 --> 00:57:19.791
Big trek down-- (SCREAMS)

1029
00:57:19.792 --> 00:57:20.957
Oh. shit!

1030
00:57:20.958 --> 00:57:24.749
- (SHOUTING)
- (SCREAMING)

1031
00:57:24.750 --> 00:57:26.957
Oh. shit! Shit. here!

1032
00:57:26.958 --> 00:57:29.458
- (SCREAMING)
- Here. Grab on.

1033
00:57:30.000 --> 00:57:30.874
Grab my hand.

1034
00:57:30.875 --> 00:57:32.749
- (SHRIEKING)
- Over here. grab on.

